text: Sæbøvik is a village in Kvinnherad municipality in Vestland county, Norway. The village is located on the narrow, western part of the island of Halsnøya, about west of the village of Høylandsbygd and immediately east of the village of Eidsvik. The village is located at the southern end of the Halsnøy Tunnel. The village has a population (2019) of 492 and a population density of . This makes it the largest urban area on the island, just after the neighboring village of Eidsvik ==References== Category:Villages in Vestland Category:Kvinnherad
